Paul Barreira, Professor of Psychiatry at Harvard Medical School and Director General of University Health Services, said the university had decided to introduce the course after finding that students suffered from severe sleeplessness during the week.
The course time consists of various interactive exercises.
One of the sections presents the image of a dormitory containing different objects (coffee bars, curtains, basketballs, books...) on which students click to know the effects of caffeine and light, as well as the impact of the lack of sleep on their physical performance and the importance of integrating a routine before bedding.
