According to him, the culture of the pride of "a white night" still exists, and he adds that modern technology and the ever-increasing pressure on students make the lack of sleep a growing problem.
Having enough and good quality sleep should be the "secret weapon" of students to fight stress, exhaustion and anxiety, he said - even to avoid taking weight, because the lack of sleep puts the brain in a mode of inanimation, making them hungry at all times.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old California student in chemistry and physical biology, helped Professor Czeisler design this course after being one of his students last year, during his first year at Harvard.
