Information point on the red tide: Low concentrations in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota
The most recent report of the Florida Fisheries and Wildlife Commission indicates a general decrease in red tide concentrations in certain areas of the Tampa Bay region.
According to the CPF, more irregular flowering conditions are reported in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte, and Collier counties, which cause decreased concentrations to occur.
